CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 3, 1958, pg. 20A, reads: "Thrush Visits Courier - Pretty Barbara McNair, Coral recording artist and recent singing star of the Broadway play, "The Body Beautiful," stopped by The Pittsburgh Courier office to chat with The Courier's George E. Pitts, last week. Bill Powell, Radio Station WEEP program director, is at right.  Miss McNair was seen on TV's "Jack Paar Show" Monday night. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Barbara McNair wearing light colored flecked dress with cowl neck, standing in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper office
